@lap v0.3
# Machine-readable API spec. Each @endpoint block is one API call.
@api SqlManagementClient
@base https://management.azure.com
@version 2017-03-01-preview
@auth OAuth2
@common_fields {resourceGroupName: any # The name of the resource group that contains the resource. You can obtain this value from the Azure Resource Manager API or the portal., serverName: any # The name of the server., subscriptionId: any # The subscription ID that identifies an Azure subscription., api-version: any # The API version to use for the request.}
@endpoints 12
@toc subscriptions(12)

@endpoint GET /subscriptions/{subscriptionId}/resourceGroups/{resourceGroupName}/providers/Microsoft.Sql/servers/{serverName}/databases/{databaseName}/extendedAuditingSettings/{blobAuditingPolicyName}
@desc Gets an extended database's blob auditing policy.
@required {databaseName: any # The name of the database., blobAuditingPolicyName: any # The name of the blob auditing policy.}
@returns(200) Successfully retrieved the extended database blob auditing policy.

@endpoint PUT /subscriptions/{subscriptionId}/resourceGroups/{resourceGroupName}/providers/Microsoft.Sql/servers/{serverName}/databases/{databaseName}/extendedAuditingSettings/{blobAuditingPolicyName}
@desc Creates or updates an extended database's blob auditing policy.
@required {databaseName: any # The name of the database., blobAuditingPolicyName: any # The name of the blob auditing policy., parameters: map # The extended database blob auditing policy.}
@returns(200) Successfully set the extended database blob auditing policy.
@returns(201) Successfully created the extended database blob auditing policy.

@endpoint GET /subscriptions/{subscriptionId}/resourceGroups/{resourceGroupName}/providers/Microsoft.Sql/servers/{serverName}/databases/{databaseName}/extendedAuditingSettings
@desc Lists extended auditing settings of a database.
@required {databaseName: any # The name of the database.}
@returns(200) Successfully retrieved the database extended auditing settings.

@endpoint GET /subscriptions/{subscriptionId}/resourceGroups/{resourceGroupName}/providers/Microsoft.Sql/servers/{serverName}/extendedAuditingSettings/{blobAuditingPolicyName}
@desc Gets an extended server's blob auditing policy.
@required {blobAuditingPolicyName: any # The name of the blob auditing policy.}
@returns(200) Successfully retrieved the extended server blob auditing policy.

@endpoint PUT /subscriptions/{subscriptionId}/resourceGroups/{resourceGroupName}/providers/Microsoft.Sql/servers/{serverName}/extendedAuditingSettings/{blobAuditingPolicyName}
@desc Creates or updates an extended server's blob auditing policy.
@required {blobAuditingPolicyName: any # The name of the blob auditing policy., parameters: map # Properties of extended blob auditing policy}
@returns(200) Successfully updated the extended auditing settings.
@returns(202) Updating the extended auditing settings is in progress.

@endpoint GET /subscriptions/{subscriptionId}/resourceGroups/{resourceGroupName}/providers/Microsoft.Sql/servers/{serverName}/extendedAuditingSettings
@desc Lists extended auditing settings of a server.
@returns(200) Successfully retrieved extended server auditing settings.

@endpoint GET /subscriptions/{subscriptionId}/resourceGroups/{resourceGroupName}/providers/Microsoft.Sql/servers/{serverName}/auditingSettings/{blobAuditingPolicyName}
